article.headline: UC Irvine 64, UC Riverside 48
article.story: IRVINE, Calif. (AP) -- Adam Templeton and Michael Hunter scored 11 points apiece to lead UC Irvine to a 64-48 victory over UC Riverside on Thursday. Darren Fells added 10 rebounds for the Anteaters (9-10, 3-2 Big West), who have won five of their past seven games. Henrik Thomsen scored 10 points and Chris Johnson added nine for the Highlanders (3-16, 0-6), who lost their 14th consecutive game. Irvine took a 10-0 lead in the first 4:43, with Templeton scoring six points during that run, and held a 20-7 advantage with 9:06 left in the first half. Riverside used a 9-2 surge to narrow the deficit to 22-16 with 3:38 left in the first half. But the Anteaters responded with another 10-0 run to build a 32-16 lead with 1:19 before halftime. Irvine outscored Riverside 20-5 in the first 8:12 of the second half to extend its lead to 52-23 with 11:48 to play. The Highlanders failed to score for a span of 5:44. The Anteaters shot 50 percent but Riverside shot 31.6 percent and a season-low 21.1 percent from 3-point range.
